review_blob: Dank, citrusy, floral goodness in a glass! Sweetness to it that makes you want more!!

Mild tartness/sour to it. Little or no peach. Which is weird since they use 12,000 lbs of peaches supposedly. Not worth the sticker price in my opinion. There are a lot better examples of this style for less money.
Tasty pale ale that pour to a redish tint. Good flavor with a burst of a citrus maybe grapefruit?
Very drinkable IPA. Sweetness & bitterness in a near perfect balance. Definitely a go to IPA!
beer_name: Cigar City Jai Alai India Pale Ale

review_blob: Tasty creamy vanilla porter that is smooth in your mouth as it goes down. Definitely recommend it!
A good dark beer flavor with a light beer drinkablitity! I tried it and drank it the rest of the night!
beer_name: Schell Anniversary Series #3 - Bavarian Forest Dampfbier
